casebody.data:
Joseph Lipkin vs. I. Nathans. Suffolk. March 9, 1925. May 20, 1925.

Present: Rugg, C.J., Crosby, Carroll, Wait, & Sanderson, JJ.

*286B. Ginsburg, for the defendant. W. L. Berger & B. Spinoza, for the plaintiff. Wait, J.

This court cannot review the findings of fact. *287There was evidence which, if believed, fully supports them. The refusals to find and rule in accordance with the defendant’s requests were proper. There is nothing in the case which calls for discussion.

Order dismissing report affirmed.
